  "referred_to_by": [
    {
      "type": "LinguisticObject",
      "content": "A large-format finished drawing on paper (251 x 410 mm) by **Adriaen van Ostade** (Haarlem, 1610 – Haarlem, 1685), dated **1673**, depicting a tavern interior with peasants drinking and dancing: drinkers at a table (left), a dancing couple (center), furniture (right), and musicians near a fireplace (background). Executed in pen in brown, watercolor wash, opaque paint, and pen in gold — the gold framing lines being a distinctive feature of Van Ostade's autonomous presentation drawings. Designated one of Teylers' **50 Topstukken**.",
